data.title: Rep. Henry Cuellar
data.meta_description: Read about Rep. Henry Cuellar. See his birthplace, home city, religion, professional experience, political experience, education, family, date of birth, and committees.
data.text:
PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

Adjunct Professor, International Commercial Law, Texas Agricultural and Mechanical International University, 1984-1986 Instructor, Department of Government, Laredo Community College, 1982-1986 Attorney, Law Office of Henry Cuellar Arbitrator/Mediator Businessman Licensed United States Customs Broker

POLITICAL EXPERIENCE

Representative, United States House of Representatives, 2004-present Candidate, United States House of Representatives, District 23, 2002 Secretary of State, State of Texas, 2001 Representative, Texas State House of Representatives, 1987-2001 Texas Delegate, National Democratic Convention, 1992 Sustaining Member, Texas Democratic Party, 1984

EDUCATION

PhD, Government, University of Texas-Austin, 1998 JD, University of Texas-Austin, 1981 MBA, International Trade, Texas Agricultural and Mechanical University, 1982 BS, Foreign Service, Georgetown University, 1978 AA, Political Science, Laredo Community College, 1976
